    characterPoints: 6,
    move: 10,
    equipment: "Knife (STR+1), jewelers tools",
    capsule: "At 13, Odea is a coltish, somewhat awkward girl with black hair cropped close to her skull. Very self-conscious, she tends to make mistakes when she thinks others are watching; left to herself she moves like an athlete. Rags make up her Port Town wear, but she has two nice outfits for hawking jewelry on the main concourse. Now an orphan, Odea arrived on Cloud City at age six when her mother — captain of a stock light freighter — fled their homeworld after her father's death, hoping to find a safer home. Her mother unknowingly carried goods stolen from Jabba the Hutt; Toin ne Yerres sent Glongfurrp to track her down and kill her. Odea, playing with friends, was warned not to return to the ship. The ship was gutted by scavengers and the *Happy Failure* now serves as a gambling casino. Odea makes intricate jewelry from electronic and metal scraps and sells it to tourists directly — she prefers not to deal with middle-men. Most read her as shy, but she has one focus: seeking her mother's killer and exacting revenge.",
    source: "WEG40119 Galaxy Guide 2: Yavin and Bespin p.90"
