    move: 10,
    equipment: "Blaster pistol (4D), flight suit, comlink",
    capsule: "Tenk Lenso was Rogue Eleven, previously a Y-wing gunner with the Deretta Destroyers — a mixed X- and Y-wing squadron known for proton torpedo strikes on Imperial depots. The Destroyers were largely routed when the Empire deployed an Interdictor cruiser on their last run; all twelve Destroyers fell during the agonizing wait for the strike force to arrive. Tenk's Y-wing shields were overloaded and the pilot killed; trapped with a locked ejection mechanism, Tenk had to crawl over his dead pilot and manually fire the ejection system while a TIE fighter lined up for the kill. He was rescued by a Rebel medical frigate but suffered psychological scars that left him unable to operate from the gunner's seat again. Transferred to Hoth, he flew an X-wing with Rogue Group instead. His snowspeeder was one of the first to fall during the Battle of Hoth.",
    source: "WEG40125 Galaxy Guide 3: The Empire Strikes Back p.35"
