    equipment: "Comlink (on belt), work clothes, various starship repair tools, datapad, 100 credits, magnetic grapplers, fusion welder (5D damage, 1 meter range)\n\nGallofree Yards Service Shuttle 23K\nCraft: Gallofree Yards Service Shuttle 23K\nType: Orbital service shuttle\nScale: Starfighter\nLength: 18 meters\nCrew: 1\nPassengers: 6 (or cargo)\nCargo Capacity: 1 metric ton (or passengers)\nConsumables: 1 day\nHyperdrive Multiplier: None\nNav Computer: None\nManeuverability: 1D\nSpace: 2\nAtmosphere: 225; 650 kmh\nHull: 1D+1\nShields: None\nSensors:\n  Passive: 10/1D\n  Scan: 15/1D+2\n  Search: 20/2D\n  Focus: 1/2D+2\nWeapons: None",
    capsule: "Ohwun's family has owned Docking Bay 94 for generations — his parents before him, and his grandmother before them. The De Maals are hardworking, decent beings who want nothing more than to have the gangsters and the civil war go away. As this does not look likely, they are considering alternate avenues, but aren't really sure what they want. Ohwun is married to Chachi, and together they run the docking bay operations and associated warehouses. They are devout Duros who follow in the traditions of their folks — walk quietly, talk quietly, play fairly.",
    source: "WEG40069 Galaxy Guide 7: Mos Eisley p.29-31"
