    capsule: "Mopiin is a middle-aged Sullustan with extreme wrinkles around the eyes and an apparent distaste for cleanliness. He bought Heff's Souvenirs from Tebbi (Heff's daughter) after Heff was killed in an unfortunate incident involving bounty hunters. The shop is a junk store offering old bannisters, ancient holovid players, cracked mirrors, and tacky souvenirs — but Mopiin makes his real living through forgery. He can forge false Tatooine township IDs for 100 credits, false Tatooine passports for a minimum of 200, and docucards for other worlds at correspondingly higher prices. Forgeries normally require at least a full day's notice. Mopiin became skilled in forgery after a short stint in a prison colony, where the food rationing system forced him to develop a barter skill. A nervous little being with a perpetual squint and hunched back, he laughs a lot for no apparent reason. His objective is to remain indispensable in Mos Eisley so he can continue to indulge in 'antiques.'",
