    capsule: "Dom always looks like he has just crawled out from underneath a leaking cargo ramp — covered in fluid and grease, with sweat trickling down his nose. He is always chewing on a cigarra (he never smokes them), and all of his pockets are full of tools. One of the best starship mechanics in all of Mos Eisley, his docking bay is used almost exclusively for repairs, with underground rooms full of repair tools, labor and engineering droids. He has a distrust of most organics and prefers droid labor. He charges about 125% of average rates, but his work is first-class and guaranteed. Determined and tough, he doesn't like people questioning his abilities — if someone argues about the quality of his work, he doubles his price. The adjacent Dockside Cafe hosts spacers and serves as a meeting place for hiring smugglers, frequented by those newer to the business who take on more dangerous missions for lower fees. The cafe bartender is a bitter droid named CG-X2R.",
