    darkSidePoints: 0,
    characterPoints: 8,
    move: 9,
    equipment: "Agri-kit (+1D to survival), powerstaff (STR+2D damage). Home contains a miniature ecosystem with artificial pond, carnivorous plants, and a semi-intelligent Vesuvague Hanging Tree (DEX 5D+1, PER 2D, STR 4D+2, vines 4D+2 damage, digestive juices 6D+1 damage) guarding a secret room where Rebel agents seek refuge.",
    capsule: "An Ithorian of some age and grace, Momaw has a sandy-brown color typical of Ithorians who spend time away from their homeworld. His dual-throated stereo voice is unmistakable. Momaw was herd leader of Tafanda Bay, a grand visitor center on Ithor. When the Imperials demanded the agricultural secrets of the Ithorians, Momaw knew that to refuse would mean the destruction of Tafanda Bay and the loss of many lives. He complied and the Ithorians banished him. He moved to Tatooine to nurse his pride and set up contacts with the Alliance. He also fell in love with Slag Flats, a Tatooine settler and one of the original colonists. Since her death, he has slowly realized he was using Slag as a diversion from his feelings. He knows the time is nearing when he must return to the Mother Jungle and prove his value. A lonely, gentle Ithorian in self-inflicted exile, his objective is to regain his place among his people so they agree to his anti-Imperial position.",
    source: "WEG40069 Galaxy Guide 7: Mos Eisley p.73"
