    equipment: "Imperial Arms Model 22T4 hold-out blaster (3D+1 damage), encrypted comlink, high-quality evening gown (in storage), ISB security code cylinder, 1,000 credits",
    capsule: "Elena Shelvay has shoulder-length blonde hair, blue eyes, and a slim athletic build. She is Jedi Corwin Shelvay's younger sister. When Corwin first came under suspicion, she was caught by High Inquisitor Tremayne as he rounded up and murdered Corwin's parents. Recognizing her usefulness, Tremayne sent her to COMPNOR's Imperial Security Bureau Re-Education bureau for indoctrination. There she came to blame her parents' deaths on Corwin — not the Empire — because he had turned to rebellion and engaged in illegal activities. She now works for the Surveillance branch of the ISB, posing as Moff Balfour's personal aide. A little disjointed and disoriented at times from Re-Ed's ministrations, she is nonetheless frighteningly loyal to Emperor Palpatine's New Order ('To serve the Emperor is sufficient justification for any action'). Her main ambition is to capture and execute her brother — her hatred is so intense that a tearful reunion between the two is highly unlikely.",
    source: "WEG40063 Galaxy Guide 9: Fragments from the Rim p.25"
