    capsule: "Thalassian slavers are an undisciplined bunch who frequently resort to full-fledged piracy — sometimes out of necessity, sometimes because they think it's fun. In some sectors, Imperials shoot Thalassian vessels on sight; in others, the reverse is true. Their most noted ship is the Harmzuay, an old Kaloth-style battlecruiser up-gunned to the point that it can destroy Nebulon-B frigates and give a Victory-class Star Destroyer a nasty fight. The name is a joke — 'Harm's Way.' Once a ship drops out of hyperspace in front of it, the Harmzuay launches fighters and cripples the vessel or uses tractor beams, then the Thalassians board once the crew is sufficiently terrified. Fighter pilots fly modified Z-95 Headhunters (maneuverability 1D+2, space 7, hull 4D, shields 1D+2, 2 triple blasters FC 1D damage 4D, concussion missiles FC 1D damage 7D).",
    source: "WEG40063 Galaxy Guide 9: Fragments from the Rim p.60-61"
