    capsule: "Galasett is a hunter who hunts other bounty hunters. This apparent contradiction of the creed stems from his friendship with Reglis Taal, whose brother was needlessly killed by hunters pursuing a mistaken bounty. Had they confirmed their information, they would have learned the posting was an error — instead they murdered Taal's brother in cold blood. While Taal dealt with the two himself, Galasett saw this injustice and decided to keep other hunters in line. He carefully watches for signs that a hunter has broken Imperial law, gets a bounty placed on the offender, then hunts them down before they know what's happened. He has been fined several times for excessive damages and served a short imprisonment for straying into a 'No Hunt Zone.' Has a bitter ongoing rivalry with the Barabel hunter Baraduk — a savage clash left both seriously wounded, and unfinished business between them will likely end in one of their deaths.",
