    capsule: "Malis is a former Imperial army trooper — the lone survivor when his platoon was ambushed by Alliance partisans on Keskin. Disgusted with the Empire's ineffectual handling of the Rebellion, he deserted, took the name Malis, and began working independently. He has gained quite a reputation in a few years. One trademark is a personal superstition regarding his 'lucky' blaster carbine — convinced that if it's ever lost or malfunctions, his career is over. Prefers the 'secret hand' approach, surprising targets when his deadly traps are sprung. Hunts only Rebel Alliance sympathizers or operatives.",
