    capsule: "No species is perhaps more naturally suited to bounty hunting than the Defel — beings that appear almost to be shadows, moving nearly invisibly. Few beings know the Defel are real, believing them spacers' legends. Morr has found the field to her liking. Her first acquisition was a trader who broke his word with several Defel — she hounded him, captured him, and brought him to the Defel people for punishment. She has preyed on the unsuspecting ever since. Has a personal preference for hunting on planets with vast subterranean complexes. Fiercely loyal to her few friends and contacts, contemptuous of those who do not keep their word.",
    source: "WEG40073 Galaxy Guide 10: Bounty Hunters p.77-78"
