    specialAbilities: "Guarded at all times by a custom-built assassin droid disguised as a protocol unit (all stats 2D except: blaster 8D, cultures 5D, languages 7D; armor +3D Strength; hidden blaster rifles 8D damage, range 3-30/100/300).",
    forcePoints: 1,
    characterPoints: 10,
    move: 10,
    equipment: "Comlink, datapad, sporting blaster (3D+1), 10,000 credits",
    capsule: "Jeslor Salaktori is the quintessential bounty hunter businessman. His position as CEO was inherited as birthright, but he has proven an adept and skillful leader. He maintains House Salaktori's dominance through three pillars: membership restricted to only the very best hunters (selected personally by Jeslor), willingness to confront Imperial officials in defense of his hunters (including pressure to limit 'collateral damage' fines), and the guild's unofficial motto — 'We take care of our own, one way or the other.' No one responsible for a Salaktori hunter's death has survived more than one year; all such deaths have been ruled 'accidental.' A ruthless corporate operator, he has directed the collapse of three minor rival houses and decreed bans on numerous occasions, motivated by a desire to hand a more powerful guild to whichever of his children proves ruthless enough to run the family business.",
    source: "WEG40073 Galaxy Guide 10: Bounty Hunters p.99-100"
