    equipment: "Hold-out blaster (3D+1), comlink, datapad, 5,000 credits",
    capsule: "Parmella Trillidor started out as an outlaw tech in the Kibilini sector. Through a series of influential marriages (six in 10 years), the ambitious Parmella gained control of enough voting blocks to have herself elected to the Kibilini Smugglers' Guild directorate. After learning of Manliss's plans to corner the spice trade in the neighboring Portmoak sector, she attempted to steer her guild's membership into an exclusive arrangement with Manliss. When many members proved reluctant, Parmella split the guild. Taking her followers with her, she migrated to the Portmoak sector, leaving a weakened Kibilini guild to fend for itself. She won an exclusive smuggling contract from Sehvorah in a heated game of suvac. Though presently content with her guild's arrangements within the cartel, her restless nature will make it impossible for her to stay content for very long — she has already confided to her closest friends concerning Artur Manliss. Is he slated to be husband number seven?",
