    capsule: "Few outside his own clan mourned the death of Jabba the Hutt. One person who was positively delighted was the Rodian Revidjasa. This one-armed veteran of covert syndicate wars had lived uncomfortably under Jabba's thumb for many years. Once a formidable gangster in several Mid-Rim sectors, Revidjasa had earned high profits in slaving and extortion operations until Jabba systematically eliminated his inner circle and forced him into servitude. Following Jabba's death, Revidjasa cemented key alliances with various Zygerian and Thalassian cartels, effectively giving him control over Jabba's slaving empire in the Mid-Rim with strong Outer Rim connections.",
