    forcePoints: 0,
    characterPoints: 15,
    move: 1,
    equipment: "Comlink, datapad, Hutt floater",
    capsule: "Seen by many as Jabba's 'heir apparent' despite rival clan affiliations, Jelasi long advocated the need to 'legitimize' as many of Jabba's criminal operations as possible. While this often provoked clashes with Jabba over policy, Jabba acknowledged this Hutt's insight into big business. With Jabba's death, Jelasi stepped in to take command of the Ig'zxyck Flare criminal syndicate, which specialized in control of legitimate businesses in several Mid-Rim sectors. He has embarked on an active program of 'legitimization' of other criminal organizations under his control. Those who refuse are quickly and quietly eliminated. This policy has incurred the wrath of several important clans — including Kumac's — who prefer a more old-fashioned way of doing Hutt business: intimidation.",
