    capsule: "Wedge Antilles grew up in a Corellian spaceport, losing his parents when a pirate vessel caused an explosion at their fueling depot. He used insurance credits to buy a stock light freighter, but when money ran out he became a weapons runner for the Rebel Alliance. One of the original Red Squadron pilots at Yavin, he became fast friends with Luke Skywalker. When Luke resigned his commission to pursue Jedi studies, Wedge took command of Rogue Squadron — the elite starfighter group they built together. He refused to re-equip with newer A- and B-wings, keeping his pilots in their battered X-wings. He has turned down promotion after promotion, refusing to give up the squadron he made famous. Of the original Red Group, only a few faces remain — Hobbie and Janson still fly with Rogue Squadron. Wedge prefers to be where the action is, handling the missions no one else can do.",
    source: "WEG40131 The Thrawn Trilogy Sourcebook p.40"
