    capsule: "Pash Cracken is the son of legendary Alliance commander General Airen Cracken. He enrolled at the Imperial Vensenor Sector Naval Academy under a false identity, excelling in starfighter tactics with innovative, unorthodox and often reckless approaches. He graduated in the top one percent of his class and was commissioned into the Imperial Navy. Shortly after, Pash and his entire TIE wing — nearly 72 pilots and ships — defected to the Alliance, an incident that supposedly attracted Lord Vader's personal attention. The Cracken Flight Group distinguished itself in hit-and-fade runs at the Xyquine system, where Pash developed the 'Cracken Twist' maneuver to evacuate the base without losses. After Endor, the group was stationed at Generis to defend the Outer Rim comm center, which fell to Grand Admiral Thrawn's forces — a huge loss to the New Republic's communications network. Pash has flame-red hair, green eyes, and a somewhat sarcastic attitude toward superior officers.",
