    capsule: "Captain Pellaeon never wanted to rule the Empire. When the commander of the Chimaera was killed over Endor, Pellaeon assumed command and was one of the few Imperial commanders prudent enough to retreat. For five years he struggled to hold the shattered remnants together, ordering retreat after retreat as the Empire was reduced to a quarter of its original size. He was more than happy to turn command over to Grand Admiral Thrawn when the Warlord returned from the Unknown Regions. He learned to admire Thrawn's tactical mind and complex plans, though he didn't always understand how the Grand Admiral reached his conclusions. After Thrawn's death, Intelligence lost sight of Pellaeon and the Chimaera.",
    source: "WEG40131 The Thrawn Trilogy Sourcebook p.64"
