    move: 10,
    equipment: "Blaster pistol (4D), comlink, datapad, Kern's Pride (modified freighter)",
    capsule: "Samuel Tomas Gillespee is a relatively well-known smuggler, usually described as 'less-than-honorable' by fellow smugglers, though with affection rather than distrust. He made a name for himself with spectacular Kessel run exploits — though most don't know he never touched his freighter's controls. He made an even bigger name by skipping the system with his partner's cut of the profit. He now handles administrative duties rather than hands-on runs, mostly because he is a spectacularly unlucky and unskilled pilot. Despite his reputation as a con artist, he treats his crew well, commanding over 20 ships. He had retired to the farming planet Ukio, but when the Imperials subjugated it and the presence of clones unnerved him, he joined Karrde's smuggler coalition. 'I don't happen to think people ought to come off an assembly line, thanks. And if they did, I sure as mynocks wouldn't put the Empire in charge of the factory.'",
    source: "WEG40131 The Thrawn Trilogy Sourcebook p.101"
