    move: 14,
    equipment: "Knife (STR+1D), comlink",
    capsule: "Rukh, clan Baikh'vair, was one of Grand Admiral Thrawn's earliest recruits when he discovered the homeworld of the Emperor's dreaded Death Commandos. Unintimidated by Imperial high technology, Rukh impressed the Grand Admiral and was made his personal bodyguard. Rukh speaks in a deep, gravelly, catlike voice, with large dark eyes and a protruding jaw filled with glistening needle teeth. He has long arms with steel-wire muscles beneath dark gray skin, hiding a slender assassin's knife in the sleeve of his tunic. When informed of the Empire's treachery against the Noghri people, Rukh volunteered to 'monitor' Thrawn — waiting for the moment the Grand Admiral learned of the Noghri betrayal before striking with his assassin's knife. Rukh is now something of a legend among the Noghri. To slay a hated enemy in his own stronghold is an act of incredible bravery — the greatest possible hunt, worth dying for.",
    source: "WEG40131 The Thrawn Trilogy Sourcebook p.165"
