    capsule: "Ekhrikhor, clan Bakh'tor, is one of the most fearsome Noghri warriors. He revels in combat and the thrill of the hunt, having tracked and killed the Empire's targets for nearly a decade. More pragmatic than most Noghri, he has operated in the galaxy long enough to absorb some morals and norms of other species. He does not take the Emperor's deception as personally as the rest — he understands why Palpatine did what he did, though expediency is not a legitimate excuse to lead an entire people to slaughter. Most recently sighted on Wayland, he cleared the path to Mount Tantiss for Luke Skywalker, Han Solo, Chewbacca, Lando Calrissian, and Mara Jade — removing lethal obstacles without the Republic operatives knowing they were under Noghri protection. Only Luke's Force skills revealed their presence. Ekhrikhor considers it a great honor to have participated in the battle and has great respect for Skywalker and Solo.",
